    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Intermittent electrical buzzing without visible damage can be a tricky, low-level issue, often related to electrical impedance or a failing bearing inside the motor. It could be a problem with the motor's internal winding insulation starting to degrade, or even a loose connection somewhere in the wiring harness that is vibrating. Honestly, these subtle issues are often best diagnosed with specialized tools, like an ammeter, which is why a professional technician is the safest bet. For a quick check, ensure all visible wires connected to the unit are firmly seated.",
